Barcelona think Frenkie de Jong will end up moving to Manchester United this summer, it has been claimed. Erik ten Hag’s side have been chasing the 25-year-old throughout the transfer window so far. However, despite agreeing a fee with their La Liga counterparts, the Red Devils are yet to get a deal over the line. Manchester United quickly earmarked De Jong as their top target back in May, shortly after it was confirmed Ten Hag would be the club’s permanent replacement for Ole Gunnar Solskjaer. Yet while they’ve agreed to pay £63million for the Netherlands international, the saga continues to drag on. It’s an open secret that De Jong is reluctant to leave Barcelona, having long dreamed of playing for the Catalan giants ever since he was a youngster. But COPE journalist Helena Condos Edo has claimed on Twitter that, over at the Nou Camp, they think the 25-year-old will end up making the move to United in the end. “Barca has NOT yet ruled out the sale of Frenkie De Jong,” she said. “They trust the Club that @DeJongFrenkie21 ends up changing its mind. Man Utd transfers: Barcelona draw up De Jong punishment plan “Although, for now, it is still closed in on the sidelines and [he] maintains that it wants to stay.” Barcelona have been saying publicly that De Jong isn’t up for sale. But the reality is that, due to their financial situation, the Catalan giants are open to cutting the former Ajax star loose. Big things were expected of De Jong when Ernesto Valverde snapped him up back in the summer transfer window of 2019, beating Manchester City and Paris Saint-Germain to the midfielder in the process. Yet the Netherlands international has often struggled for consistency under the likes of Xavi, Ronald Koeman, Quique Setien and Ernesto Valverde so far. At Ajax, De Jong established himself as one of the best players in world football under Ten Hag. DON’T MISSMan Utd have just seven players worth keeping under Erik ten HagMan Utd set price tag for Ronaldo to leaveMan Utd have 