is prove they can improve players. He [Ten Hag] can certainly do that, he’s done that at Ajax. “I think he will be looking at a player like James Garner and thinking, ‘I can prove that I can build a player into, not just a normal squad, but into a Manchester United squad that’s trying to build and get back up there’. “It’s happened before with young players at Manchester United. That’s potentially the way he wants to build. “I think James Garner is a fantastic player. I’m not comparing him with Frenkie de Jong, but there’s potential that he can grow into that position and play a similar role.” Want the latest football news? Join our brand new Facebook group by clicking here